column5: well when i go its always after the walleye season here on quinte normally mar 3 then agian on the 6th great fishing ,never been skunked yet.  white fish are alot of fun and easy to catch,the later the better i think heres a link to a site that is simcoe based and i have to say mostly innisfil www.gofishont.com  tell them hawg sent ya lol.  Hawg Hunter

I have been here a short time and I would like to know what G2G weekend is?I heard a charitable event of some sort,love to go,meet and greet and bring the kids  Or is strictly for admins and invited parties only.A tourney of some sort?

PLEASE POST THIS AT THE TOP MODS.  I WILL TAKE CARE OF THE 2010 G2G.  I,LL STEP UP AND TAKE CHARGE.   THOSE THAT WISH TO FISH OUT OF INNISFIL.  10 BUCKS FOR PARKING, WHAT EVER.    AS LONG AS IT,S AT THIS LOCAL.(BEST LOCAL AS MENTIONED FOR A SHORT WALK TO CATCH ALL)  THERE WILL BE A 10 DOLLAR ENTRY FEE.  BIGGEST ONE FISH OF ANY SPIECES.LENGHT.  ONE FISH WINS.  WINNER TAKES 50% OF THE POT.THE REST GOES TO THE TYLER FUND.(SRY IF I SPELT IT WRONG MO)  START TIME WILL BE 7 AM TIL 1 PM.  IT,S  ABOUT FUN AND MEETING FELLOW MEMBERS.  MYSELF AND THE MRS,S WILL BE PARKED AT THE BOAT RAMP,RED F150 TO COLLECT. AFTER THAT YER ALL ON YER OWN.JUST BE BACK  AT 1 PM.  THEM ARE THE RULES.FOR NOW.

What's a Whitefish???

Well I guess the moniker under your Avatar isn't worth a pinch of possum poop, an "Imperial Angler" and can't google whitefish...   Whitefish,  looks like a silvery carp with a sort of sucker mouth, hoever the meat is more white, great deep fried or smoked.

Now the only issue with Innisfil, they have passed the $10 parking fee at Innisfil Beach Park, no idea how and when they are going to start to collect it.  So, something to think about for the future when picking a place to hold a charity type event, I don't know if there's a way to circumvent this issue.  I know from the last couple of years at the tyler event, we had a lot of folks use that parking lot and this might turn a number of people off the event. Just my politely written thoughts, 'cause you can imagine the plethora of explitives I was forced to withhold.
